# P2P Attendance Application Deployment

<br>

## Deploying the Index Server
1. Run the IndexServer.py file and enter an IP address.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

2. The index server will start running.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Deploying the Peer
### Event Coordinator Processes
1. Run the Peer.py file. Then, enter an IP address, unused port number, and the IP address of the index server.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

2. The first peer to connect to the index server is considered the event coordinator (peer 0) and has the ability to start the meeting.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

3. The event coordinator will be updated with the number of attendees every time a new peer connects to the index server.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

4. When the event coordinator starts the meeting, they will receive a message from the index server confirming the start.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)


### Event Attendee processes
1. Run the Peer.py file. Then, enter an IP address, unused port number, and the IP address of the index server. 
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)


2. A new event attendee will be notified of their peer ID, then they will wait for instructions from the event coordinator.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

3. Event attendees will be notified that the meeting has started, then be prompted to send an image to 2 other peers.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

4. After an image has been successfully sent, the sending peer will receive acknowledgement messages confirming a sent image.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

5. The receiving peers will have to confirm the sending peer's attendance.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

6. After answering the prompt, the receiving peers will get a message from the index server confirming that a message to update the sending peer's attendance was sent.
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
